The questions must only come from the Kanji already learnt.
The question types should be randomly chosen, so there is no pattern to the questions, for example if the quiz has 10 questions, there should be 2 of each type, or 3 of one type and 2 of another, etc. The distribution should be as even as possible.

Setting the number of questions the quiz will have is done through telegram interaction, after user writes /quiz the bot must give it an option to choose from 4 numbers: 8, 13, 17, 21, when chosen the quiz should pull the exact amount of questions, possibly from google API to formulate the questions much better. We currently already have this functionality, but I am not sure how this works, so we need to make sure it works properly.

After the quiz is over, the Telegram bot should send another message congratulating the winner, and offering insight into the match stats(explained later).

The leaderboard itself should contain statistical information and should be a clickable navigation in the UI, to take you to another page, where you will see stats:

a) how many questions the person has answered in total (all time & per quiz)
b) how many Kanji we have learned (as this will be the same for both since the chat current Kanji is the truth)
c) What's the correct to wrong ratio (all time & per quiz)

These should also be available for each of the previously set question types, so the players have information on who answers listening questions better, or writing for example and who needs to improve on which skill. The Ui should reflect this and the filters must be easily accessible. This should egb available on a seperate page, which is also accessed once the quiz is finished and the results are shown, there is another button that says see more stats or something like that and takes the uzer to the statistics page.

